Package com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Adapter<F,T>
    This Adapter interface takes something and turns it into anther type, state in the generic types.
    Factory<F,T>
    A Factory interface is used, to create any Object.
    MultipleConnections
    This interface describes, that the inherited Class is capable of creating new Connections, based upon the Session.
    Mutex
    This interface provides an mechanism to acquire any Object at runtime to ensure Thread-Safety.
    ReceivePipeline<T>
    A ReceivePipeline differs from the Pipeline, by the Class, which they hold.
    RemoteObjectAccess
    This interface provides an way of getting RemoteObjects.
    RemoteObjectRegistration
    Any Implementation of this Interface will handle the Registration of RemoteObjects at the Server-Side and therefor the delegation and Handling of RemoteAccessCommunicationRequests
    SendBridge
    This Class is used to abstract the Send-mechanism.
    SimpleFactory<T>
    Likewise to the Factory, this Class creates a new object declared using the generic type upon calling the SimpleFactory.create() method.
    SocketFactory
    This Method is nearly the same as an Socket.
    SoftStoppable
    This Method defines a stoppable Action
    TriConsumer<T,U,V>
    This interface is created equally to the Consumer, but excepting 3 types as arguments
    TriPredicate<T,U,V>
    This interface is created equally to the Predicate, but excepting 3 types as arguments
